WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.480 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.480 --> 00:00:15.376 align:middle line:90%


00:00:15.376 --> 00:00:19.640 align:middle line:10%
>> This is "Book Tours,"
and I'm Corinne Edwards.

00:00:19.640 --> 00:00:24.420 align:middle line:10%
Mention John Steinbeck, and
everyone recognizes the name.

00:00:24.420 --> 00:00:29.220 align:middle line:84%
But what the world does not know
is the story behind his stories

00:00:29.220 --> 00:00:32.560 align:middle line:84%
and the effect of his
fame on his family.

00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:37.240 align:middle line:84%
Nancy Steinbeck, the widow of
his son, John Steinbeck IV,

00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:41.260 align:middle line:84%
tells it all and heard book,
"The Other Side of Eden."

00:00:41.260 --> 00:00:44.770 align:middle line:84%
It's a tale of love,
devotion, and the devastation

00:00:44.770 --> 00:00:47.070 align:middle line:90%
of alcoholism on a family.

00:00:47.070 --> 00:00:49.180 align:middle line:84%
And as many of you
know, you don't

00:00:49.180 --> 00:00:52.150 align:middle line:84%
have to be famous to
experience this problem.

00:00:52.150 --> 00:00:54.402 align:middle line:84%
Nancy, welcome to
Wisdom Television.

00:00:54.402 --> 00:00:55.610 align:middle line:90%
>> It's wonderful to be here.

00:00:55.610 --> 00:00:56.410 align:middle line:90%
Thank you, Corinne.

00:00:56.410 --> 00:00:58.180 align:middle line:90%
>> What a fabulous book.

00:00:58.180 --> 00:00:59.910 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm glad you liked it.

00:00:59.910 --> 00:01:02.150 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, when
your husband died,

00:01:02.150 --> 00:01:07.280 align:middle line:84%
he was in process of
writing his autobiography.

00:01:07.280 --> 00:01:10.205 align:middle line:84%
And what prompted
you to pick it up?

00:01:10.205 --> 00:01:12.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I had actually
made a promise to him.

00:01:12.660 --> 00:01:14.240 align:middle line:10%
He died in a back operation.

00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:17.990 align:middle line:10%
And before he went in for
surgery, I suddenly had a--

00:01:17.990 --> 00:01:20.090 align:middle line:10%
well, based on a dream
I'd had that night

00:01:20.090 --> 00:01:25.380 align:middle line:10%
about our German shepherd puppy
dying, and a voice saying,

00:01:25.380 --> 00:01:27.290 align:middle line:10%
I'm taking my angel back today.

00:01:27.290 --> 00:01:29.830 align:middle line:84%
And you're not supposed to
feel sorry for yourself.

00:01:29.830 --> 00:01:32.060 align:middle line:84%
This is part of
the greater plan.

00:01:32.060 --> 00:01:35.960 align:middle line:84%
And I said to John
that morning, what

00:01:35.960 --> 00:01:38.990 align:middle line:84%
happens if something-- what
should I do about your book?

00:01:38.990 --> 00:01:40.095 align:middle line:90%
And he said, finish it.

00:01:40.095 --> 00:01:41.220 align:middle line:90%
He didn't even miss a beat.

00:01:41.220 --> 00:01:42.740 align:middle line:90%
It was just like, finish it.

00:01:42.740 --> 00:01:44.270 align:middle line:90%
So I knew when he died--

00:01:44.270 --> 00:01:46.312 align:middle line:84%
>> And this was not a
life-threatening operation.

00:01:46.312 --> 00:01:47.112 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:01:47.112 --> 00:01:48.040 align:middle line:90%
>> --he was having.

00:01:48.040 --> 00:01:50.900 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there was no reason for
you to have this premonition.

00:01:50.900 --> 00:01:53.326 align:middle line:90%
>> No, it was back surgery.

00:01:53.326 --> 00:01:55.080 align:middle line:90%
>> That's amazing.

00:01:55.080 --> 00:01:56.880 align:middle line:84%
So the book is it's
very interesting

00:01:56.880 --> 00:02:00.510 align:middle line:84%
because it's his
book, but you fill

00:02:00.510 --> 00:02:05.470 align:middle line:84%
in the blanks of what happened
in between in both your lives.

00:02:05.470 --> 00:02:08.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, because he had
only finished about 50%

00:02:08.820 --> 00:02:09.990 align:middle line:90%
of the autobiography.

00:02:09.990 --> 00:02:14.230 align:middle line:84%
So the chapters are interwoven,
and there's the two voices.

00:02:14.230 --> 00:02:21.270 align:middle line:84%
>> It seems that both you and
your late husband John came

00:02:21.270 --> 00:02:24.240 align:middle line:84%
from similar backgrounds
of dysfunctional,

00:02:24.240 --> 00:02:25.920 align:middle line:90%
severely dysfunctional families.

00:02:25.920 --> 00:02:31.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, a lot of abuse, a lot of
boundaries crossed that should

00:02:31.290 --> 00:02:35.150 align:middle line:84%
never have been crossed, and
alcoholism, severe alcoholism.

00:02:35.150 --> 00:02:38.710 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, they say that 98%
of families are dysfunctional

00:02:38.710 --> 00:02:39.510 align:middle line:90%
today.

00:02:39.510 --> 00:02:39.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:02:39.920 --> 00:02:40.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Do you agree with that?

00:02:40.830 --> 00:02:41.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:02:41.630 --> 00:02:43.466 align:middle line:90%
I think 100%.

00:02:43.466 --> 00:02:45.810 align:middle line:84%
Oh, I think if you haven't
worked on yourself,

00:02:45.810 --> 00:02:49.770 align:middle line:84%
it's just normal, because it's
a generational pattern that

00:02:49.770 --> 00:02:51.330 align:middle line:90%
just goes through.

00:02:51.330 --> 00:02:54.840 align:middle line:84%
I think that consciousness has
changed in the last generation.

00:02:54.840 --> 00:02:57.450 align:middle line:84%
So those of us that are
raising kids now, especially

00:02:57.450 --> 00:02:59.610 align:middle line:84%
in the boomer generation,
I think we really

00:02:59.610 --> 00:03:02.290 align:middle line:84%
did come to some sort
of point where we said,

00:03:02.290 --> 00:03:03.570 align:middle line:90%
this will not be passed on.

00:03:03.570 --> 00:03:04.800 align:middle line:90%
It stops here.

00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:05.980 align:middle line:90%
It stops with my generation.

00:03:05.980 --> 00:03:09.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think people are
less now blaming their families

00:03:09.840 --> 00:03:12.030 align:middle line:84%
for their problems
than they did before?

00:03:12.030 --> 00:03:12.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:03:12.900 --> 00:03:15.660 align:middle line:84%
I think there is more a point
where you have to stop saying,

00:03:15.660 --> 00:03:18.450 align:middle line:84%
I was the victim, and
poor me, and saying, I

00:03:18.450 --> 00:03:19.600 align:middle line:90%
am not going to do this.

00:03:19.600 --> 00:03:22.415 align:middle line:84%
I am not going to
replicate those patterns.

00:03:22.415 --> 00:03:24.150 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, one of
the things that you--

00:03:24.150 --> 00:03:26.240 align:middle line:84%
very interesting to
me, one of the things.

00:03:26.240 --> 00:03:30.070 align:middle line:84%
You said there were rules of
dysfunctional families, three

00:03:30.070 --> 00:03:30.870 align:middle line:90%
rules.

00:03:30.870 --> 00:03:33.927 align:middle line:84%
>> Don't talk, don't
trust, don't feel.

00:03:33.927 --> 00:03:36.510 align:middle line:84%
Don't talk about the elephant
in the living room, whether it's

00:03:36.510 --> 00:03:38.730 align:middle line:84%
daddy's drinking or
mom's rageaholism,

00:03:38.730 --> 00:03:42.450 align:middle line:84%
or little brother
acting out all the time.

00:03:42.450 --> 00:03:44.160 align:middle line:90%
Don't talk about it.

00:03:44.160 --> 00:03:47.310 align:middle line:90%
And don't trust your instincts.

00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:50.220 align:middle line:84%
Listen to what the family tells
you, because it's like a cult.

00:03:50.220 --> 00:03:53.220 align:middle line:84%
They will tell you how this is
to be treated, how things are

00:03:53.220 --> 00:03:54.990 align:middle line:90%
to be swept under the carpet.

00:03:54.990 --> 00:03:56.070 align:middle line:90%
And don't feel.

00:03:56.070 --> 00:03:57.780 align:middle line:84%
Don't pay attention
to your feelings.

00:03:57.780 --> 00:04:00.630 align:middle line:84%
Because god forbid if
you feel your feelings,

00:04:00.630 --> 00:04:03.636 align:middle line:84%
the truth will come out,
and you will be shunned.

00:04:03.636 --> 00:04:04.600 align:middle line:90%
>> By society?

00:04:04.600 --> 00:04:05.815 align:middle line:90%
>> No, by the family.

00:04:05.815 --> 00:04:06.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, by the family.

00:04:06.880 --> 00:04:09.370 align:middle line:84%
>> It's like a cult. You
know, we don't talk about

00:04:09.370 --> 00:04:10.170 align:middle line:90%
daddy's drinking.

00:04:10.170 --> 00:04:12.310 align:middle line:90%
We don't talk about mom's anger.

00:04:12.310 --> 00:04:14.946 align:middle line:84%
We don't talk about
mom's pill problem.

00:04:14.946 --> 00:04:16.475 align:middle line:90%
>> Now, having--

00:04:16.475 --> 00:04:19.120 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a thing of,
our family is perfect.

00:04:19.120 --> 00:04:20.529 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:04:20.529 --> 00:04:22.750 align:middle line:84%
Or if it's not, we don't
want to recognize it.

00:04:22.750 --> 00:04:24.361 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:04:24.361 --> 00:04:29.095 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think that this is
true in all alcoholic families?

00:04:29.095 --> 00:04:32.170 align:middle line:84%
>> I think if there has not been
awareness and there hasn't been

00:04:32.170 --> 00:04:36.936 align:middle line:84%
therapy or involvement in
a 12-step program, yes.

00:04:36.936 --> 00:04:40.630 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, you mentioned in your
book here that you should have

00:04:40.630 --> 00:04:45.610 align:middle line:84%
recognized the first signs of
your husband's alcoholism when

00:04:45.610 --> 00:04:50.560 align:middle line:84%
on your first meeting, he asked
you to go out and get a bottle

00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:52.585 align:middle line:84%
of liquor for him,
and you just went.

00:04:52.585 --> 00:04:56.080 align:middle line:84%
>> Because it's normal because
I grew up in an alcoholic home.

00:04:56.080 --> 00:04:59.170 align:middle line:84%
At the time that I met
John, everyone I knew drank.

00:04:59.170 --> 00:05:00.570 align:middle line:90%
I was drinking.

00:05:00.570 --> 00:05:03.400 align:middle line:84%
It's normal that if you're
going to get together socially,

00:05:03.400 --> 00:05:06.190 align:middle line:90%
you have alcohol.

00:05:06.190 --> 00:05:08.170 align:middle line:90%
That was not a red flag to me.

00:05:08.170 --> 00:05:09.010 align:middle line:90%
Now, it would be.

00:05:09.010 --> 00:05:09.840 align:middle line:90%
>> It would?

00:05:09.840 --> 00:05:10.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:10.640 --> 00:05:11.440 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:11.440 --> 00:05:13.585 align:middle line:90%
>> But this was 25 years ago.

00:05:13.585 --> 00:05:17.470 align:middle line:84%
>> You talk about that one
of the things that you then--

00:05:17.470 --> 00:05:19.510 align:middle line:90%
you got together with John.

00:05:19.510 --> 00:05:23.100 align:middle line:84%
You fell madly in
love with each other,

00:05:23.100 --> 00:05:24.705 align:middle line:84%
and eventually
moved in together,

00:05:24.705 --> 00:05:26.850 align:middle line:90%
and eventually married.

00:05:26.850 --> 00:05:28.960 align:middle line:84%
And then you got
on this program,

00:05:28.960 --> 00:05:31.860 align:middle line:84%
which was fascinating
to me, of what you

00:05:31.860 --> 00:05:35.850 align:middle line:84%
referred to as magical
thinking, following

00:05:35.850 --> 00:05:37.240 align:middle line:90%
the gurus of the world.

00:05:37.240 --> 00:05:38.300 align:middle line:90%
Tell us about that.

00:05:38.300 --> 00:05:41.610 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, John and I met at
a Buddhist seminary that was

00:05:41.610 --> 00:05:45.540 align:middle line:84%
given by Trungpa Rinpoche, who
was the notorious crazy wisdom

00:05:45.540 --> 00:05:48.030 align:middle line:84%
girl who founded Naropa
University in Boulder,

00:05:48.030 --> 00:05:51.510 align:middle line:84%
Colorado, which is a
quite well-known center

00:05:51.510 --> 00:05:54.120 align:middle line:90%
for contemplative studies.

00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:56.010 align:middle line:84%
And he was an
outrageous alcoholic,

00:05:56.010 --> 00:05:58.810 align:middle line:84%
and he never made any
bones about hiding it,

00:05:58.810 --> 00:06:00.090 align:middle line:90%
Trungpa Rinpoche.

00:06:00.090 --> 00:06:03.210 align:middle line:84%
So people would say,
well, yes, he drinks.

00:06:03.210 --> 00:06:05.800 align:middle line:84%
But he doesn't hide it,
so what's wrong with that?

00:06:05.800 --> 00:06:07.980 align:middle line:84%
Well, many of us that
were attracted to him--

00:06:07.980 --> 00:06:11.550 align:middle line:84%
and there were thousands, and
it was right about the time

00:06:11.550 --> 00:06:13.740 align:middle line:84%
that John and I
met there was 1975.

00:06:13.740 --> 00:06:15.730 align:middle line:90%
It was like the hip place to be.

00:06:15.730 --> 00:06:17.775 align:middle line:84%
It was like a
spiritual Woodstock.

00:06:17.775 --> 00:06:22.440 align:middle line:84%
Baba Ram Dass, and all the
beat poets and musicians,

00:06:22.440 --> 00:06:23.430 align:middle line:90%
everyone came there.

00:06:23.430 --> 00:06:27.210 align:middle line:84%
And it was the greatest
thing since the '60s.

00:06:27.210 --> 00:06:30.180 align:middle line:84%
He was very
charismatic, Trungpa.

00:06:30.180 --> 00:06:32.880 align:middle line:84%
And we, again, we
thought it was normal.

00:06:32.880 --> 00:06:34.800 align:middle line:84%
Hey, we came from
a drinking culture,

00:06:34.800 --> 00:06:36.390 align:middle line:90%
and now our guru drank.

00:06:36.390 --> 00:06:37.800 align:middle line:90%
That's great.

00:06:37.800 --> 00:06:39.970 align:middle line:10%
And he did have a
very enlightened side.

00:06:39.970 --> 00:06:42.930 align:middle line:10%
There is no doubt about it
that the man was a genius.

00:06:42.930 --> 00:06:45.385 align:middle line:84%
But he was also a
severe alcoholic.

00:06:45.385 --> 00:06:46.745 align:middle line:90%
>> And a womanizer.

00:06:46.745 --> 00:06:50.160 align:middle line:84%
>> And a terrible womanizer,
which again was accepted

00:06:50.160 --> 00:06:51.765 align:middle line:90%
by the community as normal.

00:06:51.765 --> 00:06:53.640 align:middle line:84%
>> That was a sexual
revolution at that time.

00:06:53.640 --> 00:06:54.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:06:54.380 --> 00:06:55.922 align:middle line:84%
>> And that was also
very acceptable.

00:06:55.922 --> 00:06:57.645 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly, exactly.

00:06:57.645 --> 00:07:01.170 align:middle line:84%
>> So tell me the progression
of what happened here.

00:07:01.170 --> 00:07:04.230 align:middle line:84%
You started following
these gurus.

00:07:04.230 --> 00:07:07.635 align:middle line:84%
You went all over the world
seeking some of them out.

00:07:07.635 --> 00:07:10.148 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we were mostly
students of Trungpa Rinpoche's.

00:07:10.148 --> 00:07:11.940 align:middle line:84%
And then when we traveled
around the world,

00:07:11.940 --> 00:07:16.320 align:middle line:84%
we met other gurus, other
lamas of that lineage.

00:07:16.320 --> 00:07:18.510 align:middle line:84%
But he was predominantly
the one we followed.

00:07:18.510 --> 00:07:22.230 align:middle line:84%
And again, when a child comes
from an alcoholic family,

00:07:22.230 --> 00:07:24.630 align:middle line:84%
they're always
looking for utopia,

00:07:24.630 --> 00:07:27.390 align:middle line:84%
because we were
used to dystopia.

00:07:27.390 --> 00:07:30.120 align:middle line:84%
So we're always looking for the
good mommy or the good daddy.

00:07:30.120 --> 00:07:32.730 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
these gurus set up.

00:07:32.730 --> 00:07:35.040 align:middle line:90%
They promised enlightenment.

00:07:35.040 --> 00:07:38.280 align:middle line:84%
They say they will do it for
you as long as you give them

00:07:38.280 --> 00:07:41.130 align:middle line:84%
your first born child, and all
your devotion, and your money.

00:07:41.130 --> 00:07:43.140 align:middle line:90%
>> And your money.

00:07:43.140 --> 00:07:46.050 align:middle line:84%
>> But again, I have to
say this was 20 years ago.

00:07:46.050 --> 00:07:47.940 align:middle line:90%
This was hip.

00:07:47.940 --> 00:07:48.900 align:middle line:90%
This was the hip thing.

00:07:48.900 --> 00:07:55.080 align:middle line:84%
This is when Mia Farrow and the
Beatles were flocking to India.

00:07:55.080 --> 00:07:56.640 align:middle line:84%
And we thought that
we were getting

00:07:56.640 --> 00:07:59.820 align:middle line:84%
away from the functionality
of our parents

00:07:59.820 --> 00:08:01.573 align:middle line:84%
by following a system
that was exotic.

00:08:01.573 --> 00:08:03.240 align:middle line:84%
>> And nobody over
30 was to be trusted.

00:08:03.240 --> 00:08:04.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:08:04.140 --> 00:08:05.070 align:middle line:90%
And this was exotic.

00:08:05.070 --> 00:08:07.545 align:middle line:84%
Our parents couldn't
even pronounce the words

00:08:07.545 --> 00:08:09.340 align:middle line:84%
in the language
we were learning.

00:08:09.340 --> 00:08:14.760 align:middle line:84%
So it was a rebellion against
the religion of our childhood.

00:08:14.760 --> 00:08:16.720 align:middle line:84%
But we woke up all of a
sudden, and guess what?

00:08:16.720 --> 00:08:17.520 align:middle line:90%
We.

00:08:17.520 --> 00:08:19.980 align:middle line:84%
Were right back in the
system of our childhood

00:08:19.980 --> 00:08:21.660 align:middle line:84%
don't talk, don't
trust, don't feel.

00:08:21.660 --> 00:08:24.510 align:middle line:84%
Don't talk about the guru's
drinking or womanizing,

00:08:24.510 --> 00:08:25.650 align:middle line:90%
or you will be shunned.

00:08:25.650 --> 00:08:27.340 align:middle line:84%
And exactly the
same thing happened.

00:08:27.340 --> 00:08:31.530 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, Andrew Harvey
wrote the open for your book,

00:08:31.530 --> 00:08:33.039 align:middle line:90%
the forward.

00:08:33.039 --> 00:08:36.929 align:middle line:84%
And one of his
greatest cries today

00:08:36.929 --> 00:08:42.419 align:middle line:84%
is that don't trust anybody who
claims to be a teacher if they

00:08:42.419 --> 00:08:47.320 align:middle line:84%
ask for money, if
they ask for sex,

00:08:47.320 --> 00:08:48.790 align:middle line:84%
or if they tell
you what to think.

00:08:48.790 --> 00:08:50.996 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:08:50.996 --> 00:08:55.510 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, do you think that those
people, that type of guru,

00:08:55.510 --> 00:09:00.535 align:middle line:84%
that type of spiritual leader,
is it still happening today?

00:09:00.535 --> 00:09:03.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, it absolutely
is happening.

00:09:03.920 --> 00:09:07.630 align:middle line:84%
And I think that the people that
are entrenched in those systems

00:09:07.630 --> 00:09:09.700 align:middle line:90%
are in such denial.

00:09:09.700 --> 00:09:12.700 align:middle line:84%
And they don't want to
face the pain of having

00:09:12.700 --> 00:09:16.960 align:middle line:84%
to deal with the
bleakness of coming

00:09:16.960 --> 00:09:19.660 align:middle line:84%
to some understanding
of the divine

00:09:19.660 --> 00:09:24.190 align:middle line:84%
or what sustains you
spiritually on your own.

00:09:24.190 --> 00:09:28.060 align:middle line:84%
That's very difficult. I
mean, when my husband died,

00:09:28.060 --> 00:09:31.000 align:middle line:84%
it was not Buddhism
that sustained me

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:34.570 align:middle line:84%
through that tremendous
shock and horror of losing

00:09:34.570 --> 00:09:35.770 align:middle line:90%
the beloved.

00:09:35.770 --> 00:09:39.070 align:middle line:84%
I was turning to this
12-step program which

00:09:39.070 --> 00:09:42.940 align:middle line:84%
forces you to define a
higher power according

00:09:42.940 --> 00:09:44.320 align:middle line:90%
to your understanding.

00:09:44.320 --> 00:09:46.510 align:middle line:84%
Not to scripture,
not to what you've

00:09:46.510 --> 00:09:49.540 align:middle line:84%
been told in classes and
by the guru in lectures,

00:09:49.540 --> 00:09:53.110 align:middle line:84%
but what through the very
darkest night, what sustains

00:09:53.110 --> 00:09:55.686 align:middle line:90%
you, how you understand God.

00:09:55.686 --> 00:09:58.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think that you had
a different experience with

00:09:58.250 --> 00:09:59.050 align:middle line:90%
alcoholism?

00:09:59.050 --> 00:10:03.520 align:middle line:84%
Because let's face it, both
of you came from rich people,

00:10:03.520 --> 00:10:05.590 align:middle line:90%
came from the privileged class.

00:10:05.590 --> 00:10:09.130 align:middle line:84%
Do you think you had
a different experience

00:10:09.130 --> 00:10:13.450 align:middle line:84%
with the damage of alcoholism
because of the money?

00:10:13.450 --> 00:10:14.650 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:10:14.650 --> 00:10:16.600 align:middle line:84%
I don't think
money, fame, nothing

00:10:16.600 --> 00:10:20.080 align:middle line:84%
masks the veneer of the
pain of an alcoholic family.

00:10:20.080 --> 00:10:23.432 align:middle line:84%
I think you scratch the
surface, and it's all the same.

00:10:23.432 --> 00:10:27.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Everybody comes
down to zero here.

00:10:27.330 --> 00:10:28.130 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:10:28.130 --> 00:10:32.000 align:middle line:84%
>> I want to talk about
alcoholism and how your husband

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:36.700 align:middle line:84%
really got sober in a minute,
but we have to take a break.

00:10:36.700 --> 00:10:38.070 align:middle line:90%
It's a fascinating story, Nancy.

00:10:38.070 --> 00:10:38.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:10:38.870 --> 00:10:42.560 align:middle line:84%
>> We're talking to Nancy
Steinbeck about her fabulous

00:10:42.560 --> 00:10:44.620 align:middle line:90%
book, "The Other Side of Eden."

00:10:44.620 --> 00:10:45.420 align:middle line:90%
Stay with us.

00:10:45.420 --> 00:10:47.450 align:middle line:90%
It's a compelling story.

00:10:47.450 --> 00:10:49.180 align:middle line:90%
We'll be right back.

